# -------------------------
# Recommended exceptions (what to commit)
# -------------------------
# Keep lockfiles for reproducible builds
!pnpm-lock.yaml
!package-lock.json
!yarn.lock
!poetry.lock

# Keep migrations folder and SQL files (explicitly)
!supabase/migrations/
!supabase/schema.sql

# Keep infra configs, Dockerfiles, CI workflows
!infra/
!docker-compose.yml
!Dockerfile
!.github/workflows/

# -------------------------
# Helpful reminders (not part of ignore rules)
# -------------------------
# - NEVER commit your secrets or service keys. Use your CI/CD provider's secrets store.
# - Keep DB migrations and infra config (render.yaml, vercel.json) in the repo.
# - If you add generated files you DO want to commit (e.g., a generated API client),
#   add an explicit "!" rule above to override the general ignore.

